1
00:00:24,020 --> 00:00:25,900
Mmm...

2
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:34,330
Ow... ouch...

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,420
I see.

4
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,630
So your old salon is trying
to scout you back.

5
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:47,720
Yes, that's right...

6
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:50,630
That's the situation. I'm sorry.

7
00:00:51,470 --> 00:00:53,680
No, that's amazing.

8
00:00:54,310 --> 00:00:56,470
They even have customers requesting you.

9
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:58,770
That means they really value you.

10
00:01:00,140 --> 00:01:02,900
If that's the case, wouldn't it be
better for you to go back?

11
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:04,900
Is that really okay?

12
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:06,530
Oh, I mean...

13
00:01:06,610 --> 00:01:09,070
That's for you to decide, Hirayama.

14
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:14,870
It'll be a loss for us, but you know...

15
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:19,000
Maybe this is the right timing.

16
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:22,790
When things start moving
smoothly like this

17
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:25,420
you might regret it 
if you don't take the chance.

18
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:31,720
This place is so comfortable to work at,
so honestly, I'm hesitant to leave.

19
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:37,600
And I escaped my previous job due to issues,
so I'm a bit anxious about going back...

20
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:40,680
Hm, did you really escape though?

21
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,520
What?

22
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:45,310
I mean, if you're reconnecting
 with your old workplace,

23
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:50,400
maybe this was just a necessary detour
on your path forward.

24
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:55,120
If that's the case, maybe it's worth
trying again there?

25
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,830
...That's what I think, anyway.

26
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:05,290
Honestly, I've been really torn about this.

27
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,960
I still have unfinished business with hairstyling.

28
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:13,430
I understand.

29
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,300
I should go back.

30
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:24,480
Thank you for everything.
I'm grateful for your support.

31
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:27,570
What? Akari, you're quitting?

32
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:28,820
Akari, you're leaving?

33
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:31,780
No, today's not my last day.

34
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,240
But why?

35
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,280
- I want to work with you more.
- I'll miss you.

36
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,740
It's complicated.

37
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:38,950
I can't work
without you here, Akari.

38
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,740
That's no good. You need to work.

39
00:02:47,410 --> 00:02:52,260
Okubo Ayano - Missed Call Yesterday

40
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:52,260
A detour... was it?

41
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:23,280
Okubo Ayano
Delete Contact

42
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,370
Deleted

